post_text:
We are excited to welcome back all of our students to their digital classrooms! All FUESD schools have worked diligently to make digital learning as easy as possible!

Join your classroom this Monday with three easy steps:
1. Click on the "Teacher Directory" tab at the top of your school website.
2. Find your teacher and click their "website" button.
3. Click on the "Google Meet" link found on your teacher's class website.

-------

¡Estamos emocionados de dar la bienvenida a todos nuestros estudiantes a sus aulas digitales! ¡Todas las escuelas de FUESD han trabajado diligentemente para hacer que el aprendizaje digital sea lo más fácil posible!

Únase a su salón de clases en tres sencillos pasos:
1. Haga clic en la pestaña "Directorio de profesores" en la parte superior del sitio web de su escuela
2. Ecuentra a tu profesor y haz clic en su botón "sitio web".
3. Haga clic en el enlace "Google Meet" que se encuentra en el sitio web de su profesor.

post_text:
FUESD SCHOOL CLOSURES

Today, In consultation with the Public Health officials and the CDC, the Fallbrook Union Elementary School District has made a decision to close all schools, effective Monday, March 16. These school closures are being implemented in all of San Diego county to prevent potential exposure of students and staff to COVID-19. The goal is for FUESD schools to re-open Monday, April 13th.

We want you to know that schools will operate normally for the remainder of the day. All afterschool programs will be open for today but will be closed starting Monday, March 16th.

For detailed information regarding school closures please visit the FUESD district website.

Your child will also be bringing home a letter detailing school closures.

We will be sending frequent updates with information and resources via email, text messages and our website. Please be checking those frequently. We are grateful for your patience and understanding as we continue to work through this difficult situation.

post_text: Next time you find yourself in a "win or lose" situation, take a step back and see if there is a solution to everyone's problems. Odds are there is. #SevenHabits
text: Next time you find yourself in a "win or lose" situation, take a step back and see if there is a solution to everyone's problems. Odds are there is. #SevenHabits

post_text: It is easy to focus on what it urgent. This week try something different. Prioritize your life by what it most important not what is most urgent.
text: It is easy to focus on what it urgent. This week try something different. Prioritize your life by what it most important not what is most urgent.

post_text: Sometimes the answer isn't finding more time but defining what is a real priority. #SevenHabits
text: Sometimes the answer isn't finding more time but defining what is a real priority. #SevenHabits

post_text: With most endeavors in life, the battle is won or lost on your ability to organize. Schedule your life by what is most important, not what is most urgent. #SevenHabits #StephenCovey
text: With most endeavors in life, the battle is won or lost on your ability to organize. Schedule your life by what is most important, not what is most urgent. #SevenHabits #StephenCovey

post_text: This week be mindful of the habits you create. Create habits to reach new heights and help others succeed. #SevenHabits
text: This week be mindful of the habits you create. Create habits to reach new heights and help others succeed. #SevenHabits

post_text: Habit Two: When you start any project, conversation or task, think first about the desired result and then build your actions to make that result a reality. #SevenHabits #StephenCovey
text: Habit Two: When you start any project, conversation or task, think first about the desired result and then build your actions to make that result a reality. #SevenHabits #StephenCovey

post_text: Many things in life are out of our control. But much of it is. Be proactive and work for positive change in your daily circle of influence.
text: Many things in life are out of our control. But much of it is. Be proactive and work for positive change in your daily circle of influence.

post_text: Habit one sets the foundation for all others. Instead of reacting to or worrying about conditions over which they have little or no control, proactive people focus their time and energy on things they can control.
text: Habit one sets the foundation for all others. Instead of reacting to or worrying about conditions over which they have little or no control, proactive people focus their time and energy on things they can control.

post_text: To reach new heights you must first implement new habits and principles. Join all of us at #FUESD in applying the #SevenHabits today.
text: To reach new heights you must first implement new habits and principles. Join all of us at #FUESD in applying the #SevenHabits today.

post_text: So what are the #SevenHabits of Highly Effective People? These seven principles were created by best selling author and business leader Stephen Covey. Each habit is designed to help individuals reach new heights using communication, organization and self-care.
text: So what are the #SevenHabits of Highly Effective People? These seven principles were created by best selling author and business leader Stephen Covey. Each habit is designed to help individuals reach new heights using communication, organization and self-care.

post_text: For the rest of September, we are going to share the #SevenHabits of Highly Effective People. These seven principles are foundational to the success of our students and we are excited to share them with the community.

post_text: We’re proud to have Mary Fay Pendleton School, San Onofre School, and Fallbrook Homeschool Academy named as Honor Roll Schools by Educational Results Partnership, a data science organization that recognizes schools with high performance in Math and Science. Sponsored by the Campaign for Business and Education Excellence, the ERP Honor Roll is the only school recognition program in the state that uses student achievement outcome data, and is a valuable resource for all schools to identify successful peers and learn about best practices that improve student success. For more info on @edresults and the ERP Honor Roll program, visit: www.edresults.org

San Onofre School
May 24, 2018 at 9:53 AM ·

We're so proud to have the hard work of our students and teachers recognized and honored!

post_text: Congratulations to La Paloma Elementary, Mary Fay Pendleton School, San Onofre School, and William H. Frazier Elementary! We’re proud to have these schools named #ERPHonorRoll schools, which recognizes high-performing, achievement gap-closing schools across the state. The Educational Results Partnership Honor Roll, sponsored by CBEE, is the only school recognition program in California using student achievement outcomes as the criteria. The Honor Roll is a valuable resource for all schools to identify successful peers and learn about best practices that are improving student achievement. For more info on @edresults and the ERP Honor Roll program, visit: www.edresults.org .
